    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="28"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bridgman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Paz, Bolivia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 278.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that the British
                    subject, George Melville, who was imprisoned in Corocoro, charged with theft,
                    has been set at liberty after repeated requests made by me to the minister of
                    foreign relations.</p>
                <p>Melville wrote various pitiful letters, saying he was starving, etc., and begging
                    money. Quite an amount was sent him, and since then nothing has come directly
                    from him. I know, however, he has been discharged.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George H. Bridgman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
